The paper deals with the problem of Sybil detection in social networks, which is a topic related to security and privacy in online social networks. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new method for Sybil detection based on graph structure and local rule-based propagation, which falls under the scope of cs.SD (Software Engineering and Security) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper uses theoretical analysis and empirical evaluation, which are related to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
